Write a metrics framework with the following sections:

## North Star Metric
(The single metric that best captures the core value delivered to users. Name it, define it precisely, and explain why it was chosen.)

## Leading Indicators
(3–5 early-signal metrics that predict whether the North Star will be achieved. For each: name, definition, target value, measurement method.)

## Lagging Indicators
(2–3 downstream metrics that confirm long-term value delivery. For each: name, definition, target value, measurement method.)

## Counter-Metrics
(1–2 metrics to watch for unintended negative consequences — e.g. engagement up but churn also up. For each: name, why it matters, acceptable threshold.)

## Measurement Plan
(How will these metrics be collected? What instrumentation, analytics tools, or processes are required? What is the measurement cadence — daily, weekly, monthly?)

Rules:
- All metrics must be specific and measurable, not vague ("improve satisfaction" is not a metric).
- Tie leading indicators to the North Star with explicit reasoning.
